Databases A-Z

Find the best library databases for your research.

91 Databases found

All Databases

A

Academic Search Premier This link opens in a new window
Featured
EBSCO database which searches magazines and academic journals on a variety of topics. Provides access to articles on history, science, social sciences, and many more.
ACM Digital Library This link opens in a new window
The ACM (Association for Computing Machinery) Digital Library is a research and discovery platform containing: The Full-Text Collection of all ACM publications, including journals, conference proceedings, technical magazines, newsletters and books.
ASTM Compass This link opens in a new window
ASTM Compass is a vast collection of industry-leading standards and technical information produced by the American Society for Testing & Materials (ASTM International).

B

Business Source Premier This link opens in a new window
Featured
EBSCO database which provides access to full text articles from magazines and academic journals in the field of business. Includes company profiles, country reports, industry profiles, and market share reports.

C

ChiltonLibrary This link opens in a new window
Online resource for automotive repair. Includes access to step-by-step repair procedures, technical service bulletins, recalls, wiring diagrams, and more.
CINAHLPlus with Full-Text This link opens in a new window
Featured
CINAHL (Cumulative Index to Nursing and Allied Health Literature) is a comprehensive research database provides full text for nursing and allied health journals, evidence-based care sheets, quick lessons and continuing education modules.
Cochrane Library This link opens in a new window
The Cochrane Library (ISSN 1465-1858) is a collection of databases that contain high-quality, independent evidence to inform healthcare decision-making. The Cochrane Library is owned by Cochrane and published by Wiley. See whats new on the Cochrane Library.
Credo InfoLit This link opens in a new window
Information literacy modules for instruction
Credo Reference This link opens in a new window
Featured
Encyclopedias and dictionaries on a variety of topics including medicine, history, social sciences, and more.

E

EBSCO eBook Collection This link opens in a new window
Featured
Access to over 200,000 ebooks on a wide variety of topics. No e-reader required to access these materials.
EBSCO eBooks: Academic Collection This link opens in a new window
A subset of EBSCO's eBook collection that features ebooks that can be accessed by an unlimited number of users. No e-reader required to access these materials.
EBSCO Open Dissertations This link opens in a new window
EBSCO Open Dissertations contains records for more than 1.4 million electronic theses and dissertations from more than 320 universities around the world.
Education Research Complete This link opens in a new window
EBSCO database specialized for ebooks and academic journal articles in the field of education. Titles include Comparative Education, Journal of Digital Learning in Teacher Education, and Journal of Instructional Psychology.
ERIC This link opens in a new window
Education database sponsored by the US Department of Education and Institute of Education sciences. Provides access to journal articles, educational reports and research documents.
European Views of the Americas: 1493 to 1750 This link opens in a new window
European Views of the Americas: 1493 to 1750 is an archive of indexed publications related to the Americas and written in Europe before 1750. It includes thousands of valuable primary source records covering the history of European exploration as well as portrayals of Native American peoples.

F

Films on Demand This link opens in a new window
Featured
Access to over 22,000 films and documentaries on a variety of topics. Search by topic, producer, or monthly theme.

G

Gale Academic OneFile This link opens in a new window
Featured
A general subject research database which houses over 80 million articles in academic peer-reviewed journals, magazines, and newspapers on a wide variety of topics.
Gale Academic OneFile Select This link opens in a new window
A research database which provides access to over 40 million articles from academic journals and magazines in a variety of topics.
Gale Books and Authors This link opens in a new window
A research database that houses book reviews and synopses to help readers discover works of fiction and non-fiction.
Gale Business: Entrepreneurship This link opens in a new window
A business research database, covering all major areas of starting, operating and maintaining a business. Includes business plans from the Business Plans Handbook and business concepts defined in Encyclopedia of Management and Encyclopedia of Small Business.
Gale Business: Insights This link opens in a new window
Database which includes market share reports, SWOT analyses and company profiles.
Gale eBooks This link opens in a new window
A collection of in-depth encyclopedias and reference eBooks on a variety of subjects: history, environmental sciences, social studies, health, religion, and world cultures.
Gale General OneFile This link opens in a new window
A general subject research database with access to 160+ million articles from magazines and journals on a variety of subjects.
Gale Health and Wellness This link opens in a new window
Alternate Name(s) Health and Wellness Resource Center
A health database housing both consumer and professional sources. A good starting point for background on specific medical conditions and types of treatments and alternative therapies.
Gale In Context: Biography This link opens in a new window
Alternate Name(s) Biography In Context
A research database with biographies and information for over 600,000 people. Features pages on artists, politicians, and other famous figures.
Gale In Context: College This link opens in a new window
Alternate Name(s) College in Context
A research database that combines reference content with full-text magazines, academic journals, news articles, primary source documents, images, videos, audio files and links to vetted websites.
Gale In Context: Opposing Viewpoints This link opens in a new window
Featured
Alternate Name(s) Opposing Viewpoints in Context
A research database specializing in current events and topics under debate. Includes opinion essays, news articles, and videos providing facts and arguments for both sides of a debate.
Gale In Context: Science This link opens in a new window
Alternate Name(s) Science In Context
A research database providing an overview of topics related to most fields of science. Includes access to full-text articles from academic peer-reviewed journals, eBook chapters and media.
Gale In Context: U.S. History This link opens in a new window
Alternate Name(s) U.S. History In Context
A research database which houses magazines, journals, and some encyclopedia content on various topics in United States history.
Gale LegalForms This link opens in a new window
Access a wide selection of state-specific (and multi-state) legal forms and resources across the most popular legal areas.
Gale OneFile: Agriculture This link opens in a new window
A research database that houses journals on a variety of agricultural topics, from practical aspects of farming to cutting-edge scientific research in horticulture.
Gale OneFile: Business This link opens in a new window
A research database which houses magazines and journals on a variety of business topics.
Gale OneFile: Communications and Mass Media This link opens in a new window
A research database which houses magazines and journals about a variety of communication, technology, and media-related topics.
Gale OneFile: Contemporary Women's Issues This link opens in a new window
New
Find timely and historically relevant content on issues that influence womens lives across the globe.
Gale OneFile: Criminal Justice This link opens in a new window
A research database which houses magazine and journal articles on a variety of criminal justice topics.
Gale OneFile: Culinary Arts This link opens in a new window
A research database that offers a variety of information from major cooking and nutrition magazines as well as book reference content from Delmar.
Gale OneFile: Diversity Studies This link opens in a new window
A research database which provides access to articles from publications that explore cultural differences and diversity.
Gale OneFile: Economics and Theory This link opens in a new window
A research database that houses periodical titles covered in the EconLit bibliographic index. Includes sources on topics such as starting a business, marketing a product, developing policy, analyzing trends, constructing economic models, investing for the future, researching rates, and more.
Gale OneFile: Educator's Reference Complete This link opens in a new window
A research database which provides access to ebooks, journal articles, and reports in the fields of education, psychology, and child development.
Gale OneFile: Entrepreneurship This link opens in a new window
A business research database, covering all major areas of starting, operating and maintaining a business. Includes business plans from the Business Plans Handbook and business concepts defined in Encyclopedia of Management and Encyclopedia of Small Business.
Gale OneFile: Environmental Studies and Policy This link opens in a new window
A research database that houses journals and reference content about environmental studies, including diverse perspectives from the scientific community, governmental policymakers, and corporate interests.
Gale OneFile: Fine Arts This link opens in a new window
A research databases that houses millions of articles at the fingertips of serious students of drama, music, art history, and filmmaking.
Gale OneFile: Gardening and Horticulture This link opens in a new window
A research database that houses sources that focus on the practical aspects and the scientific theory of horticulture studies.
Gale OneFile: Gender Studies This link opens in a new window
A research database that houses sources related to gender studies, family and marital issues, and more.
Gale OneFile: Home Improvement This link opens in a new window
A research database that houses a collection of home Improvement sources; covers topics such as architectural techniques, tool, and material selection, and zoning requirements.
Gale OneFile: Hospitality and Tourism This link opens in a new window
A research database that provides access to articles on a variety of hospitality and service industry topics, including the cultural and economic aspects of travel and tourism.
Gale OneFile: Information Science This link opens in a new window
A research database that houses content for library science students, information science students, technology professionals, and others
Gale OneFile: Insurance and Liability This link opens in a new window
A research database that houses journals which addresses concerns over the protection of assets, physical or intellectual, ranging from the individual property owner to multinational corporations
Gale OneFile: Leadership and Management This link opens in a new window
Database that houses periodical content covering topics like organizational dynamics, adult learning, and more.
Gale OneFile: LegalTrac This link opens in a new window
Law database that houses legal journals including titles like the International Journal of Law, Information Technology, and the Journal of Criminal Law.
Gale OneFile: Military and Intelligence This link opens in a new window
A research database which houses magazine and academic journal articles in the fields of war, military, and government agencies.
Gale OneFile: News This link opens in a new window
A research database for news articles on current and historical events. Includes access to local, national, and international newspapers, magazines, and media websites.
Gale OneFile: Nursing and Allied Health This link opens in a new window
A research database which houses magazine and journals on a variety of health topics and issues in the nursing profession.
Gale OneFile: Physical Therapy and Sports Medicine This link opens in a new window
A research database that provides access to academic journals and magazines covering the fields of physical therapy, physical fitness, and sports medicine.
Gale OneFile: Pop Culture Studies This link opens in a new window
A research database that provides access to scholarly journals and magazines that both analyze and contribute to popular culture.
Gale OneFile: Popular Magazines This link opens in a new window
A research database that houses magazines focusing on current events, sports, science and health issues.
Gale OneFile: Psychology This link opens in a new window
A psychology research database housing magazines and journals on a variety of topics.
Gale OneFile: Religion and Philosophy This link opens in a new window
A research database which houses magazines and journals on religious, philosophical, and ethical topics.
Gale OneFile: Science This link opens in a new window
A research database that houses articles to satisfy almost every scientific inquiry and keep researchers current. Key subjects include the biological sciences, computing, engineering, and technology.
Gale OneFile: U.S. History This link opens in a new window
A research database which houses magazines and journals on various topics in American History.
Gale OneFile: Vocations and Careers This link opens in a new window
A research database that offers hundreds of current and applicable periodicals ranging from general career guides to highly specialized industry journals.
Gale OneFile: War and Terrorism This link opens in a new window
A research databases that houses sources for analysts, risk management professionals, and students of military science, history, and social science.
Gale OneFile: World History This link opens in a new window
A research database which houses magazines and journals on various topics in World History.
GreenFILE Environmental Science Collection This link opens in a new window
Collection of journal article abstracts in the fields on the topics of global warming, pollution, recycling, and more information on the human impact on the environment.

H

Health Source: Nursing/Academic Edition This link opens in a new window
This resource provides nearly 550 scholarly full-text journals focusing on nursing and allied health.
HeinOnline This link opens in a new window
HeinOnline is a premier online research platform that provides more than 202 million pages of multidisciplinary periodicals, essential government documents, international resources, case law, and much more
Historical New York Times This link opens in a new window
Offers full page and article images with searchable full text of the New York Times back to the first issue. The collection includes digital reproductions providing access to every page from every available issue.

J

JSTOR This link opens in a new window
Featured
JSTOR is a platform for journals, books, images, and primary sources in a wide variety of subject areas in the arts, humanities, social sciences, and sciences.

K

Kanopy This link opens in a new window
Featured
Stream over 30,000 films from hundreds of popular producers such as The Criterion Collection, The Great Courses, and PBS, as well as thousands of independent filmmakers.

L

Lexicomp for Dentistry This link opens in a new window
Lexicomp for dentistry provides industry-leading reference information and screening tools to help answer your prescribing, diagnosis, and treatment questions. With dental-specific pharmacology information on over 8,000 prescription drugs, OTCs, and natural products plus exclusive tools like our state-of-the-art lesion diagnosis aid and e-Prescribe component Lexicomp has what you need to keep your patients safe.
Library, Information Science & Technology Abstracts This link opens in a new window
Library, Information Science & Technology Abstracts (LISTA) is a research database for library and information science studies. LISTA provides indexing and abstracting for hundreds of key journals, books, research reports. It is EBSCO's intention to provide access to this resource on a continual basis.
Literary Reference Plus This link opens in a new window
Alternate Name(s) Literary Reference Center Plus
Literary Reference Plus is a full-text literary database providing a complete collection of reference works across all genres and time periods. It contains thousands of poems, short stories, classic novels, plot summaries, critical essays, literary journals, reference books and author biographies, plus lesson plans and literary study guides.

M

MEDLINE This link opens in a new window
Full-text academic journal articles in the field of medicine through the EBSCO platform. MEDLINE is the US National Library of Medicine bibliographic database.
MLA International Bibliography This link opens in a new window
MLA International Bibliography is an index of scholarship on all aspects of modern languages and literature.

N

Newsbank Access World News This link opens in a new window
New Featured
NewsBank consolidates current and archived information from thousands of newspaper titles, as well as newswires, web editions, blogs, videos, broadcast transcripts, business journals, periodicals, government documents and other publications.
NewsBank: Vermont Newspapers This link opens in a new window
Search across Vermont News sources. (Note: this search does not include the Burlington Free Press - Search it directly here.)

O

OReilly for Higher Education This link opens in a new window
Featured
Includes books, videos, proven learning paths, case studies and audio books. Topics range from programming to IT networking to project management to graphic design to business strategy. Includes content published by OReilly as well as other publishers.

P

Peterson's Test and Career Prep This link opens in a new window
Search thousands of college and graduate schools, identify scholarships, take practice tests, create resumes, and explore careers.
ProCon.Org This link opens in a new window
New

ProCon.org presents sourced pros and cons of debatable issues, as well as a host of reference information relevant to those issues, thoroughly researched and compiled by their research staff and editors.

Professional Development Collection This link opens in a new window
EBSCO database specializing in trade journal and magazine articles on professional development and training for teachers.
ProQuest Ebook Central This link opens in a new window
Access eBooks purchased through Proquest. This is a small collection, primarily consisting of titles requested by faculty. No e-reader required to access these materials.
ProQuest Global Newsstream This link opens in a new window
Featured
Full text of 300+ U.S. and international news sources. Includes coverage of 150+ major U.S. and international newspapers such as The New York Times and the Times of London, plus hundreds of other news sources and news wires.
PsycArticles This link opens in a new window
Full text, peer-reviewed articles in behavioral science and mental health from the American Psychological Association and affiliated journals.
Psychology and Behavioral Sciences Collection This link opens in a new window
EBSCO database specializing in full-text journal articles in the field of psychology. Includes access to School Psychology Review and Reading Teacher.
PSYCInfo This link opens in a new window
Featured
Peer-reviewed articles in behavioral science and mental health.

S

Shopkey Pro This link opens in a new window
ShopKey Pro delivers complete OEM repair, estimating & maintenance information, along with exclusive real-world knowledge in a single lookup, to help automotive technicians repair vehicles more accurately and efficiently.
*Please not that Shopkey is only accessible on campus.
SPORTDiscus This link opens in a new window
SPORTDiscus is the leading bibliographic database for sports and sports medicine research. It includes records from leading sports medicine journals, books, dissertations and more.
Statista This link opens in a new window
Quantitative data on media, business, finance, politics, and other topics

T

Teacher Reference Center This link opens in a new window
A complimentary research database for teachers, Teacher Reference Center (TRC) provides indexing and abstracts for more than 230 peer-reviewed journals.
Truck Series This link opens in a new window
The TruckSeries software suite provides a one-stop, single log-in resource to help commercial truck service professionals estimate labor times, diagnose and repair Class 4-8 trucks more accurately and efficiently.
**Please note that access is only available on campus.

V

Vocational and Career Collection This link opens in a new window
EBSCO database specializing in full-text articles from journals and magazines to help users in researching a vocation, finding an appropriate institution of learning, job searching, and maintaining a career.
